At least eleven people have been killed and fourteen others injured after a bus and truck collided on the Badplaas Road, outside Machadodorp in Mpumalanga.On arrival paramedics found the bus lying on the side of the road while the truck had come to a stop in the middle of the road, a short distance away. Both vehicles had sustained a large amount of damage in the collision.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said: &#8220;Several passengers were trapped inside the bus while numerous more were found walking around the scene and others were trapped beneath the overturned bus.&#8221;Meiring added that paramedics discovered that a total of eleven patients sustained fatal injuries and were declared dead on the scene.Fourteen other patients who were found on the scene, two sustained critical injuries while the remaining twelve had sustained minor to moderate injuries.Advanced life support interventions was provided to the critically injured patients and others were transported by an ambulance to various hospitals in the area .The details surrounding this incident are not yet known.-TNA Reporter 